Lessons learned from COVID19 CoronavirusOutbreak EvergreenHosp : when you begin to use most(all) conventional ventilators on adults with COVID19, you need to develop a plan for pregnant mothers who might(will) deliver a preterm or critical infant that will also need a vent

COVID19 Pregnant women suspected or known to have COVID19 should notify hospitals prior to arriving to allow them time to prepare. Will affect transportation and isolation needs on arrival! Safer and faster.

COVID19 Currently reviewing facts on clinical presentation. 20% of hospitalized pts progress to more severe disease. Pregnancy is a risk for other resp infections (eg influenza and SARS). Number of pregnant woman with COVID19 isn't that high but suggest they are "at risk".
COVID19 Topic is Information for clinicians caring for pregnant women and children with the new coronavirus.
